The Seven Jehovian Seals are located at different horizontal Ley Line/ Latitude coordinates along the common vertical Axiatonal Line-7 at 70° W Longitude, which runs down the eastern Atlantic Ocean. (See Star Gates and Seals Map Appendix-3). Jehovian Seal-1, the least powerful, is located NE of Quebec, Canada at 70° W Longitude/47.08° N Latitude . Due to the May 2001 Jehovian Seal-1 release, this region is likely to experience climatic disturbances or intensification of natural weather patterns between November 2001 and May 2002, with January-February 2002 being the most vulnerable periods.
